-{"_type":"issue","id":"mindspec-9n2h","title":"[2u0u follow-up] complete close-verify should re-read via a FRESH dolt connection","description":"Spec 096's 2u0u close-verify re-reads the bead status after closing, but on the SAME dolt session/connection, which returns the optimistic in-session 'closed' even when the write does not persist to a fresh connection. Observed repeatedly during spec 097 bead completes (e.g. r04i.1): complete reported 'closed' + exit 0, but a fresh bd show showed IN_PROGRESS — required the manual bd close workaround. Harden the close-verify (internal/complete) to re-read via a fresh connection (or force a commit/flush) so the silent-close-loss is genuinely caught.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"richardmaxsteel@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-13T17:56:42Z","created_by":"mrmaxsteel","updated_at":"2026-06-13T17:56:42Z","labels":["code-review-2026-05-14"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
