 {"_type":"issue","id":"mindspec-2u0u","title":"mindspec complete reported 'closed' but the Dolt close did not persist — silent close-leg loss","description":"During spec-092 Bead 7's completion (2026-06-11 ~09:00), mindspec complete printed 'Bead mindspec-fwo5.7 closed' and exited 0, but bd show afterwards showed in_progress with closed_at None — the close leg was silently lost (also explains the empty 'Next bead ready:' line in the same output). Coverage-fixed manually with bd close. Distinct from the jsonl-lag pattern (where Dolt was correctly closed). Suspect: complete.Run's close step (bd close subprocess) failed or raced without surfacing an error — complete.go's close handling tolerates already-closed but may swallow other failures. Evidence: AUTOPILOT-LOG bead-7 completion entry. Relates to spec 092's exit-codes-never-lie invariant — candidate for a follow-up under the same contract.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"richardmaxsteel@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-11T09:54:02Z","created_by":"mrmaxsteel","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:05:52Z","closed_at":"2026-06-13T13:05:52Z","close_reason":"Fixed by spec 096 (lifecycle-correctness), merged to main in PR #141 (c5f4f9d).","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
 {"_type":"issue","id":"mindspec-perm","title":"per-bead doc-sync/ADR gates run against empty diff when complete runs from the spec worktree — vacuous passes","description":"complete.Run computes merge-base(specBranch, HEAD) from the spec worktree where HEAD==specBranch tip, so the diff is empty and the 086/087 gates pass vacuously. Every spec-092 bead complete tonight passed this way (zero override metadata on any fwo5 bead confirms). The gates only bite at impl approve (whole branch) — discovered by the 092 doc-sync pre-check 2026-06-11. Fix: anchor the per-bead diff to the bead branch's fork point or the bead worktree HEAD.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"richardmaxsteel@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-11T09:28:46Z","created_by":"mrmaxsteel","updated_at":"2026-06-13T10:24:55Z","closed_at":"2026-06-13T10:24:55Z","close_reason":"Sibling of aqey (the vacuous-pass half); spec 095 (PR #140) regression-locks the fork-anchoring against the spec-worktree empty-range vacuous pass. Done.","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
